{
  "texts": [
    "This indicates that ∼30% of the predicted score might not be accurate.",
    "Therefore, we use the original score annotation when available, and use the predicted and rescaled score only when necessary.",
    "We consider data filtering algorithms both from the instruction-tuning domain and from the preference learning domain.",
    "This include algorithms such as DEITA (Liu et al., 2024b), LONGEST (Zhao et al., 2024), ALPAGASUS (Chen et al., 2024), and ARGILLA (Argilla, 2024).",
    "We also consider A2, which can be seen as a combination of ARGILLA and ALPAGASUS: first removing pairs that has a score difference of less than two, and then sampling 10k data that has the highest chosen score in each bin."
  ]
}